sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant Cognito as AWS Cognito
    participant DefineAuth as DefineAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant CreateAuth as CreateAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant VerifyAuth as VerifyAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant EnsureUser as EnsureCognitoUser Lambda
    participant Django as Django Backend
    participant Redis as Redis (pending OTP state)
    participant PreToken as PreTokenGeneration Lambda

    Note over Browser,PreToken: User is already migrated — custom:django_id is set in Cognito

    Browser->>Cognito: InitiateAuth(CUSTOM_AUTH)<br/>{USERNAME: "user@example.com"}
    Cognito->>DefineAuth: session=[]
    DefineAuth-->>Cognito: issueTokens=false, challengeName=CUSTOM_CHALLENGE
    Cognito->>CreateAuth: session=[]
    CreateAuth->>Redis: EXISTS pending_otp:{username} → false
    Redis-->>CreateAuth: false
    CreateAuth-->>Cognito: step=PASSWORD_VERIFY
    Cognito-->>Browser: CUSTOM_CHALLENGE (PASSWORD_VERIFY step)

    Browser->>Cognito: RespondToAuthChallenge<br/>ANSWER='{"email":"user@...","password":"secret"}'
    Cognito->>VerifyAuth: step=PASSWORD_VERIFY<br/>userAttributes.custom:django_id="42" (migrated!)
    Note over VerifyAuth: is_migrated=true → Cognito-native path

    VerifyAuth->>EnsureUser: invoke(action=verify_password)<br/>{user_pool_id, client_id, email, password}
    EnsureUser->>Cognito: AdminInitiateAuth(USER_PASSWORD_AUTH)<br/>{USERNAME:"user@...", PASSWORD:"secret"}
    Cognito-->>EnsureUser: AuthenticationResult (success)
    EnsureUser-->>VerifyAuth: {success: true}

    VerifyAuth->>Django: POST /api/auth/mfa-check/<br/>{"email":"user@..."}
    Django-->>VerifyAuth: 200 {"mfa_required": false}

    VerifyAuth->>Redis: DEL pending_otp:{username} (cleanup)
    VerifyAuth-->>Cognito: answerCorrect=true

    Cognito->>DefineAuth: last.challengeResult=true
    DefineAuth-->>Cognito: issueTokens=true
    Cognito->>PreToken: PreTokenGeneration trigger<br/>userAttributes={email, custom:django_id="42", sub=cognito-uuid}

    Note over PreToken: Step 1 — Unified access gate
    PreToken->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"password"}
    Django-->>PreToken: 200 {"allowed":true}

    Note over PreToken: Step 2 — django_id already set on profile
    PreToken-->>Cognito: claimsToAddOrOverride={django_id:"42"}
    Cognito-->>Browser: AuthenticationResult<br/>{id_token, access_token, refresh_token}

    Note over Browser: Login complete. No Django password call made.
